er-play goal, when' b'a goal is scored, each skater on the ice for the scoring team is given a' b'+, and each skater on the ice for the other team is given a short-' b'handed goals do count for b'' b'q: what is the five-hole?' b"a: the space between a goalie's pads. there are five major scoring zones:" b'(1) upper left corner of goal, upper right, lower left, lower' b'right, and five-hole.' b'' b'q: what is the meaning of throwing an octopus on the ice?' b"a: this tradition began in detroit in the 1950's when two best-of-seven" b'series were required to win the stanley cup. every time detroit won a' b'game, an octopus with one less arm was thrown on the ice.' b'' b'q: who was the first woman to play in an nhl game?' b'a: manon rheaume, a 20-year-old goaltender, became the first woman ever' b'to play in an nhl game on september when she started in net for' b'the expansion tampa bay lightning in an exhibition against the st. louis' b'blues. rheaume played the first period before at the 10,400-seat' b'expo hall on the florida state fairgrounds and allowed two goals on nine' b'shots. she left with the score tied although the lightning ultimately' b'lost the game, b'' b'q: what is the richest contract in nhl history?' b'a: mario lemieux, the superstar center of the pittsburgh penguins, signed' b'the richest contract in nhl history, a seven-year deal believed to be' b'worth about million. lemieux will earn between million and b'million a year, nearly twice as much as any other player in the league.' b'' b'q: who is the new commissioner of the nhl?' b'a: gary bettman, vice president and general counsel of the national' b'basketball association, was named commissioner of the national hockey' b'league, friday, december bettman joined the nba in as' b"assistant general counsel. he became the league's chief legal officer in" b'september of a new york resident, bettman graduated from cornell' b'university in and from new york university school of law in b'' b'q: how many professional hockey leagues are there in north america?' b'a: six: national, american, international, east coast, central and' b'colonial hockey leagues.' b'' b'--------------------------------------------------------------------------' b'' b'9. miscellaneous:' b'' b'for field hockey discussions, go to the newsgroup rec.sport.hockey.field.' b'for skating discussions, go to the newsgroup rec.skate.' b'' b'some sites get another hockey group, called clari.sports.hockey. c.s.h' b'consists of the upi feed for all upi news articles that are related to' b'hockey, including game results, summaries, scores, standings, etc. much' b'of the information in the nhl team news section comes from this newsgroup.' b'' b'the rec.sport.hockey frequently asked questions posting is posted semi-' b'monthly, usually on the 1st and 15th of each month, during the hockey' b'season. this file was originally created by tom wilson, who posted it' b'during the season. it was taken over by mitch mcgowan for the' b'1992-93 season.' b'' b'--------------------------------------------------------------------------' b'' b'please make corrections via e-mail, indicating "r.s.h faq" as the' b'subject line. feel free to start a discussion on any previously mentioned' b'topic (but use an appropriate subject line).' b'' b'' b'1' b'' b'' 